  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="ITA54">
<l>veṟpeṉ ṟiruñcōlai vēṅkaṭameṉ ṟivviraṇṭu</l>
<l>niṟpeṉṟu nīmatikku nīrmaipō – ṉiṟpeṉ</l>
<l>ṟuḷaṅkōyi luḷḷamvait tuḷḷiṉēṉ veḷḷat</l>
<l>tiḷaṅkōyil kaiviṭē leṉṟu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Thinking ‘don’t abandon the temporary temple<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">This is a reference to the snake bed on which Nārāyaṇa sleeps in the ocean, which “I”, in contradistinction to my heart (= nī), see as a temple as important, or even more so, than the two temple sites Vēṅkaṭam an Iruñcōlai.</note> in the flood’,</l>
<l>I remember, having kept it in [my] heart as [my] inner temple,</l>
<l>as a station equal in essense [to those] that you esteem as stations,</l> 
<l>[namely] both these: Iruñcōlai [and] Vēṅkaṭam that are mountains.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
